# Creatalk
A full-stack video calling platform for creators and fans.

## Features
- Real-time video calls with Daily.co
- Secure payment processing with Stripe
- Advanced scheduling system
- Creator dashboard and analytics

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router) with Turbopack
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui (Zinc color scheme)
- ESLint + Prettier configuration
- Supabase (Auth, Database, Realtime, RLS)
- Daily.co (Video calling API with recording)
- Stripe (Test mode payments - one-time purchases)

## Development Strategy
### Supabase Development
- Supabase Cloudのみを使用し、ローカル環境は使用しない
- マイグレーションファイルはバージョン管理し、SQL Editorで実行
- RLSポリシーは全テーブルに適用
- Realtime機能を活用した状態同期

## Directory Structure
```
src/
├── app/                 # App Router pages
│   ├── (auth)/         # Auth route group
│   │   └── login/      # Login page
│   ├── dashboard/      # User dashboard
│   ├── creators/       # Creator listing & profiles
│   │   └── [id]/       # Creator detail pages
│   ├── creator/        # Creator management
│   │   ├── apply/      # Creator registration
│   │   ├── products/   # Product management
│   │   ├── schedule/   # Schedule management
│   │   └── earnings/   # Revenue dashboard
│   ├── call/           # Video call pages
│   │   └── [roomId]/   # Video call interface
│   ├── profile/        # Profile settings
│   └── api/            # API routes (minimal)
│       └── auth/       # OAuth callbacks only
├── components/         # React components
│   ├── ui/            # shadcn/ui components
│   ├── auth/          # Auth-related components
│   ├── call/          # Call-related components
│   ├── creator/       # Creator-specific components
│   └── layout/        # Layout components
├── actions/           # Server Actions
│   ├── auth.ts        # Authentication actions
│   ├── creator.ts     # Creator actions
│   ├── call.ts        # Call management actions
│   └── payment.ts     # Payment actions
├── lib/              # Utilities and configurations
│   ├── supabase.ts   # Supabase client
│   ├── daily.ts      # Daily.co client
│   ├── stripe.ts     # Stripe configuration
│   └── utils.ts      # General utilities
├── types/            # TypeScript type definitions
│   ├── database.ts   # Supabase database types
│   ├── auth.ts       # Auth types
│   └── call.ts       # Call-related types
└── hooks/            # Custom React hooks
├── useAuth.ts    # Authentication hook
└── useCall.ts    # Call management hook
```

## Code Style
- Use src/ directory structure
- Import alias: @/* → src/*
- Use Server Actions over API routes
- TypeScript strict mode
- ESLint + Prettier for code formatting
- Component names: PascalCase
- File names: kebab-case
- Always include proper error handling
- Use revalidatePath() for cache updates
- Use "use server" directive for server functions
- Form handling with Server Actions

## Business Logic
### Call Products (2 patterns)
1. Queue System: 21:00-22:00 time slots with breaks
2. Fixed Slots: 21:00-21:05, 21:08-21:13 specific timings

### Features Required
- Video/Audio ON/OFF control
- Screen sharing (for real-time illustration feedback)
- Chat (Creator can speak, Fan chat-only mode)
- Recording (Creator-configurable, 1-week access/download)
- Break system for queue management
- Payment before call (front-payment system)
- Real-time status updates

## Database Schema
- profiles (user info, linked to auth.users)
- creators (creator info, online status, ratings)
- call_products (type: queue/slot, pricing, recording settings)
- reservations (queue position, slot times, Daily.co room info)

## Page Structure
### Auth Pages
- /login - Email/Password + Google OAuth

### User Common Pages
- /dashboard - User-specific dashboard
- /profile - Profile settings

### Fan Pages
- /creators - Creator list with search/filter
- /creators/[id] - Creator profile & products
- /creators/[id]/products/[productId] - Purchase flow
- /call/[roomId] - Video call interface

### Creator Pages
- /creator/apply - Creator registration
- /creator/products - Product management (queue/slot types)
- /creator/schedule - Schedule management
- /creator/earnings - Revenue dashboard

## Daily.co Integration
- Room creation with recording enabled/disabled
- Participant limits (Creator + 1 Fan)
- Auto-expiry for fixed slots
- Recording URL storage and access control
- Break system for queue management

## Stripe Integration
- One-time payments for call purchases
- Test mode with test card numbers
- Webhook handling for payment confirmation

## UI Patterns
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Dark mode support
- shadcn/ui components as base
- Consistent loading states
- Error boundaries
- Real-time status updates (Supabase Realtime)
- Toast notifications for user feedback

## Development Environment
- Use Supabase Cloud (not local)
- Environment variables for API keys
- Git version control with meaningful commits
- ESLint rules for code quality

## Features Priority
1. Auth system & profiles
2. Creator listing & basic video calls
3. Payment integration & call products
4. Creator management tools & analytics

## API Strategy
- Daily.co: Video calls, recording, participant management
- Stripe: One-time payments for call purchases
- Supabase: All data operations via Server Actions
- API Routes only for: webhooks, OAuth callbacks

## Error Handling
- Try-catch blocks in Server Actions
- User-friendly error messages
- Loading states for async operations
- Form validation with proper feedback

## Testing Strategy
### Unit Testing
- Vitest for component and utility testing
- React Testing Library for component interactions
- Test coverage target: 80%+ for critical paths
- Mock Supabase and Daily.co in tests

### E2E Testing
- Playwright for end-to-end testing
- Critical user flows: auth, call booking, video calls
- Cross-browser testing (Chrome, Safari, Firefox)
- Mobile device testing

### Test Structure
```
src/
├── tests/          # Unit tests
├── components/
│   └── tests/      # Component tests
└── e2e/               # E2E tests
├── auth.spec.ts
├── booking.spec.ts
└── call.spec.ts
```

## Performance Goals
### Core Web Vitals
- LCP (Largest Contentful Paint): < 2.5s
- FID (First Input Delay): < 100ms
- CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift): < 0.1
- Lighthouse Performance Score: 90+

### Video Call Quality
- Connection establishment: < 3s
- Audio/Video latency: < 150ms
- Recording quality: 720p minimum
- Mobile compatibility: iOS Safari, Android Chrome

### Optimization Techniques
- Next.js Image optimization
- Code splitting with dynamic imports
- Supabase connection pooling
- Daily.co preconnection for faster calls

## Security Guidelines
### Authentication & Authorization
- Supabase RLS (Row Level Security) for all tables
- JWT token validation in middleware
- Session management with automatic refresh
- Role-based access control (Fan/Creator/Admin)

### API Security
- Environment variables for all API keys
- No sensitive data in client-side code
- Rate limiting for API endpoints
- Input validation and sanitization

### Data Protection
- HTTPS only in production
- Encrypted data storage (Supabase)
- PII handling compliance
- Video call data retention policies

### Security Checklist
- [ ] No API keys in git repository
- [ ] All database queries use RLS
- [ ] Input validation on all forms
- [ ] CORS properly configured
- [ ] Security headers implemented
- [ ] Regular dependency updates

