## UI Design Guidelines
### Design System Reference
- Inspiration: Vercel, Linear, Stripe, Discord UI patterns
- Modern, professional, developer-focused aesthetic
- Glass-morphism and subtle animations
- Micro-interactions for enhanced UX

### Color System
- Base: Zinc (shadcn/ui Zinc theme)
- Primary: Blue-500 (#3B82F6)
- Secondary: Zinc-500 (#71717A)
- Success: Green-500 (#10B981)
- Warning: Yellow-500 (#F59E0B)
- Error: Red-500 (#EF4444)
- Background: Dark theme preferred

### Typography Scale
- Headings: font-bold, proper hierarchy (text-3xl, text-2xl, text-xl)
- Body: font-medium for UI, font-normal for content
- Code: font-mono for technical elements
- Proper contrast ratios (4.5:1 minimum)

### Layout Principles
- 8px grid system for spacing
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Consistent component spacing
- Card-based information architecture
- Proper visual hierarchy

### Component Patterns
#### Navigation
- Sidebar navigation for dashboard
- Top navigation for marketing pages
- Breadcrumbs for deep navigation
- Mobile-friendly hamburger menus

#### Data Display
- Cards for grouped information
- Tables with sorting and filtering
- Charts for analytics (recharts)
- Progress indicators for loading
- Empty states with helpful messaging

#### Forms
- shadcn/ui form components
- Proper validation feedback
- Loading states during submission
- Error handling with toast notifications
- Accessibility compliance

#### Interactive Elements
- Hover effects with smooth transitions
- Click feedback (button states)
- Skeleton loading for async content
- Toast notifications for actions
- Modal dialogs for confirmations

### Animation Guidelines
- Subtle transitions (200-300ms)
- Easing functions: ease-in-out
- Hover effects on interactive elements
- Page transitions for route changes
- Loading animations for async operations

### Responsive Breakpoints
- Mobile: 320px - 768px
- Tablet: 768px - 1024px
- Desktop: 1024px+
- Test on multiple devices

### Accessibility Standards
- Semantic HTML elements
- ARIA labels where needed
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility
- Color contrast compliance
- Focus indicators

### Component Library
#### Required shadcn/ui Components
- card, button, input, form
- avatar, badge, progress
- dialog, sheet, tabs
- skeleton, toast, dropdown-menu
- calendar, chart (for advanced features)

#### Custom Components
- VideoCallInterface (Daily.co integration)
- CreatorCard (creator listings)
- CallProductCard (service offerings)
- PaymentForm (Stripe integration)
- StatusIndicator (online/offline states)

